<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9200, 9300, 9400 Models Built After January 1, 1995 - ELECTRICAL
        TROUBLESHOOTING CATERPILLAR 3176B AND 3406E ELECTRONIC ENGINES - DIAGNOSTICS AND TROUBLESHOOTING - CLUTCH SWITCH
        (55)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="0">
        <title>CLUTCH SWITCH (55)</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If the vehicle is equipped with an Allison transmission, this switch is replaced with a jumper
                        connection.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing Clutch Switch And Circuits</title>
            <table id="t0805724" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Test 16 - Testing Clutch Switch And Circuits</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" align="center" charoff="50" char="c">
                    <colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.80in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.80in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" colwidth="1.80in"/>
                    <spanspec namest="1" nameend="7" spanname="s1t7" align="center"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="7" spanname="s1t7">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TESTING CLUTCH SWITCH AND CIRCUITS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>At (294) disconnect clutch switch lead from cab harness. With clutch pedal
                                    released, measure resistance across clutch switch pigtail connector (A to B). Switch
                                    should read closed.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>Clutch switch, (A to B).</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;2 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>If switch is not adjusted properly, adjust and retest. (Refer to paragraph
                                    6.3.12.2 clutch switch adjustment.) If switch is adjusted properly, replace the
                                    switch.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Depress clutch pedal while measuring resistance across clutch switch pigtail (294)
                                    terminal A to B.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>Set/ resume switch 2 to 1 and 2 to 3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>If switch is not adjusted properly, adjust and retest. (Refer to paragraph
                                    6.3.12.2 clutch switch adjustment.) If switch is adjusted properly, replace the
                                    switch.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Disconnect connector (400) from ECM. At connector (400) use test lead to jumper
                                    terminal 24 to ground. At connector (294) measure resistance to ground at circuit
                                    97AH.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(294) 97AH to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate open condition in circuit 97AH between connectors (294) and (400), then
                                    correct.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>At connector (400), use test lead to jumper terminal 29 to 24. At clutch switch
                                    harness (294) measure resistance between circuit 97-GE and 97AH.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(294) 97-GE to 97AH.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 97-GE/ 97-GA/97-G between connectors
                                    (294) and (400), then correct.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Remove jumper from connector (400), but do not connect. At clutch switch harness
                                    (294), measure resistance between circuits 97AH and 97-GE.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(294) clutch switch 97AH to 97-GE.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>The clutch switch adjustment and circuits check OK.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate short circuit between circuit 97AH and circuit 97-GE, then correct.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Adjusting Clutch Switch</title>
            <para>The Clutch switch should be mounted so that the switch actuator makes contact with the clutch pedal
                arm when the arm is depressed 0.5 inch at the point of actuator contact. The bracket can be bent forward
                or backward for adjustment. An audible click (switch closing) should be heard when the pedal is
                released.
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
